parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake system can cause the brakes to lock or not engage, leading to loss of control, accidents, or difficulty moving the vehicle, which can result in injury or damage.
symptoms: The parking brakes will not disengage
the parking brakes lock while the vehicle is in motion
the parking brakes do not engage intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Overheated brakes can cause the calipers to stick, boil the brake fluid, and lead to brake failure, which can result in loss of control, accidents, or injury.
symptoms: The brakes are overheated
the calipers stick
the brake fluid boils.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fogged-up windows can reduce visibility, making it difficult to drive safely, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windows are fogged up
making it difficult to see mirrors or the road.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty brake warning light indicator can fail to alert the driver of brake system issues, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake warning light indicator is faulty
fails to illuminate
or does not provide accurate warnings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of cotter pins can lead to loose or detached components, potentially causing accidents or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Rubbing noise while driving
loose or detached components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An overloaded suspension can cause the rear springs to flatten or develop a negative bow, affecting the vehicle's stability and handling, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Rear springs are flat or have a negative bow
uneven ride
reduced stability
and handling issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected activation of the auto park brake can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The auto park brake activates unexpectedly while driving
the vehicle comes to an abrupt stop
the brake pedal feels hard or spongy
the vehicle is unable to move
the parking brake is stuck in the "on" position.
